  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "雙重束縛 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-double-bind",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / conflict / expectation / trap</p>\n    <h1>雙重束縛</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Double Bind</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當一個人同時被要求滿足彼此衝突的期待，而且不論選哪邊都會被懲罰時，問題常不在能力，而在於他被放進了無法贏的結構。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『怎麼總做不好』和『其實規則彼此打架』拆開，因為很多挫敗不是個人失敗，而是被塞進了兩頭都會挨打的要求組合。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>溝通陷阱 / 矛盾要求</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Receiving conflicting demands where either response is punished</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>要求衝突、回應空間、懲罰結構、澄清可能</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能更早辨認組織與關係中的矛盾命令，不再把無解題硬當成執行力問題</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>衝突</span>\n      <span>無解</span>\n      <span>耗損</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>最耗人的不是要求高，而是要求彼此衝突卻還假裝可以同時成立</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">雙重束縛最痛的地方，在於它讓人不論怎麼做都像在犯錯。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>表面上每一條要求都合理，但當它們在現實裡彼此互斥，執行者就會被迫承擔本該由結構面處理的矛盾。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先把兩條命令分開寫出來</strong>\n        <p>只要衝突被說清楚，無解感就比較不會全壓在人身上。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再問能否排序或取捨</strong>\n        <p>若優先序不明，就等於把矛盾外包給最末端的人。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後建立求助與澄清管道</strong>\n        <p>不能只要求執行者『自己平衡』，卻不給他調整規則的權限。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一個你同時被要求快、穩、創新又零風險的工作場景開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">雙重束縛在管理、家庭、教育與跨部門合作裡都可能出現。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>團隊被要求『自己判斷、主動決策』，但一旦沒有逐層請示又會被指責越權。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>真正卡住人的常不是不知道怎麼做，而是兩邊都會出事。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">收到彼此衝突要求</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">缺少可澄清與排序的空間</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">執行者陷入長期防衛與耗損</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>雙重束縛最值得看見的是：有些低績效是結構矛盾，不是個體懶散。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看無解要求的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">不是每個 tradeoff 都是雙重束縛，關鍵在於你是否被要求同時滿足不可兼得的事，且無法談條件。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>命令衝突度</strong>\n        <p>兩條要求是否在現實條件下根本互相排斥？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>懲罰對稱性</strong>\n        <p>是否不論選哪邊都會被負面評價？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>求助空間</strong>\n        <p>提出矛盾後，能不能真的討論優先序？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>責任位置</strong>\n        <p>矛盾是上層該解的，還是被悄悄丟給末端個人承擔？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>互斥要求</th>\n            <th>結果</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>管理</td>\n            <td>主動決策 / 不要越權</td>\n            <td>人人變得保守或過度請示</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>專案</td>\n            <td>快點交付 / 不准有任何短期風險</td>\n            <td>時程與品質都被壓成不誠實</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>協作</td>\n            <td>自己判斷 / 但要完全照我想法</td>\n            <td>對話充滿挫敗與猜心</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼雙重束縛會特別耗損</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為它不是單純高標，而是持續讓人失去可成功的參照點。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>永遠猜不對</strong>\n        <p>沒有哪種回應能穩定換到正向回饋。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>自我懷疑會累積</strong>\n        <p>人會開始以為是自己不夠好，而不是規則有問題。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>關係信任被腐蝕</strong>\n        <p>長期處在雙重束縛裡，很難再相信溝通是真誠可解的。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">雙重束縛不是一般困難要求，而是要求之間彼此打架卻又不能被明講。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把矛盾顯性化帶回管理與協作</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程團隊來說，最常見的雙重束縛往往藏在 ownership、時程與風險要求之間。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Owner 制度</strong>\n        <p>嘴上說完全授權，實際又要求所有重要決策都需逐層認可。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>品質要求</strong>\n        <p>要求零事故卻不給測試時間與回滾空間，最後只會鼓勵報告失真。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>文化口號</strong>\n        <p>說要坦誠回饋，但負面訊息一講就被處罰，久了只剩沉默。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>看到執行者長期兩頭挨打時，先別急著教他平衡，先檢查要求是不是本來就互斥。</li>\n      <li>最有效的修法通常不是鼓勵抗壓，而是把優先序、例外條件與升級路徑講清楚。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">雙重束縛不是所有 tradeoff 的別名，而是特定的無解結構。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要要求高就算雙重束縛</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。難題不等於互斥，關鍵在於要求是否同時不可滿足。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這只是個人敏感</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>若多數人都在同位置卡住，通常是結構問題。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只在家庭關係才有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>管理、專案與團隊文化中都很常見。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>這是高標挑戰，還是其實是一道結構上無法全對的題</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放在卡住的協作裡。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果我同時遵守兩條要求，真的辦得到嗎</strong>\n        <p>若辦不到，就該先上升處理規則衝突。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>當我指出矛盾時，系統允不允許我討論優先序</strong>\n        <p>如果不允許，耗損通常會持續擴大。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 role conflict、organizational ambiguity 與 psychological safety。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 double bind 為主，再把概念帶回組織管理、角色衝突與協作摩擦。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Double bind 條目整理了這種互相衝突且難以逃脫的溝通結構。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Double_bind\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Double Bind</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰概念</strong>\n        <p>Role conflict 可作為對照，理解角色要求如何彼此打架。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Role_conflict\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Role Conflict</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>安全背景</strong>\n        <p>Psychological safety 條目有助於理解為何沒有求助空間時，雙重束縛特別傷人。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychological_safety\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Psychological Safety</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個你最近最卡的要求組合，把兩條互相衝突的命令直接寫出來。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
